  "text": "Closing a chapter.\n\n After two incredible years, my journey with Groupon has come to an end due to recent team layoffs..\n\n While the news was difficult to process, I’m genuinely grateful for the experience. \nMy time at Groupon pushed me out of my comfort zone and gave me a chance to work on complex hiring challenges alongside some truly talented and efficient people - especially my closest team, Marcela and Katarína, who are both amazing recruiters and friends.\n\n Now that I’ve had some time to reflect, I’m officially #OpenToWork.\n\n I’m currently exploring Senior Talent Acquisition / Technical Recruiter roles within the Tech & IT space (bonus points for open-source-friendly companies!).\n\nWhat I bring:\n • Partnering with Engineering Managers: I don't just \"fill seats\" - I build relationships with engineering leaders to understand technical nuances.\n • Candidate Experience: A strong candidate-centric style paired with a deep understanding of modern engineering stacks.\n • AI: Leveraging AI tools to streamline sourcing and admin, allowing me to focus 100% on the human side of hiring.\n • DevRel Mindset: Driving employer branding through community building, meetups, and developer outreach.\n\n I have been working remotely for 5 years, but I am also open to hybrid work within the Brno, Czechia. \nBoth FTE and B2B arrangements are welcome.\n\n If you’d like to know what it’s like to work with me, check out the Recommendations section on my profile - my partners and candidates say it better than I ever could.\n\n#TechRecruiter #TalentAcquisition #Layoffs #OpenToWork #Brno #RemoteWork #DevRel #Hiring",
